Returns the priority assigned by the event publisher.

isPersistent

public boolean isPersistent()
Description copied from interface: Event
States whether the event should be stored or not on Server side.
Marking the event as persistent does not mean that it will not be lost but ensures just that the Server makes a best-effort to store it until the subscribers consume it.

Specified by:
isPersistent in interface Event
Returns:
true if the event is persistent, false otherwise
